<FIRST>r a AM-BRF--PlaneDown     05-16 0107</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--Plane Down,0109</SECOND>
<HEAD>Marine Jet Crashes; Pilot Ejects Safely</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HEBER SPRINGS, Ark. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A U.S. Marine Corps A-4 jet fighter
crashed on Brewer Mountain about 20 miles northwest of Heber
Springs on Monday, but the pilot ejected and was uninjured, an Air
Force spokesman said.
   The plane, assigned to Marine Air Group 42, Detachment B, at
Memphis Naval Air Station in Tennessee, was involved in local
training at the time of the accident, according to Chief Warrant
Officer Tim Butcher at Memphis NAS.
   The name of the pilot could not be obtained.
   Military and Federal Aviation Administration personnel were
investigating the cause of the crash.
</TEXT>
