<HEAD>Train-Bus Collision Reportedly Kills 47</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW DELHI, India (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A speeding train rammed into a bus
packed with wedding guests at an unmanned railroad crossing in
western Gujarat state, killing 47 people, news reports said today.
   Both Press Trust of India and United News of India said 26
people died at the scene of Monday night's crash in the remote
village of Tarsai. PTI said 21 more died later in hospitals.
   All of the dead were in a minibus and were heading home after
attending a wedding, the news agencies said. UNI said the victims
included at least nine women and 15 children.
   The injured were taken to a hospital in Porbander, the nearest
big town and birthplace of Mohandas K. (Mahatma) Gandhi, leader of
the nonviolent freedom movement that brought about India's
independence from Britain in 1947.
   Porbander is about 560 miles southwest of New Delhi on the
Arabian Sea.
