<HEAD>Dutch Tug Picks up 87 Vietnamese Refugees</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HAARLEM, Netherlands (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A Dutch tug rescued 87 Vietnamese
refugees, including an 8-month-old baby, from a boat that was
adrift in the South China Sea, the owners of the vessel said
Tuesday.
   The Santania rescued the refugees Monday after they were adrift
for three days, according to Jan Timmermans, a spokesman for the
towage company, Transport Contractors.
   The boat left Vietnam with 90 passengers, but three died before
the Dutch rescued them, Timmermans said. Several children,
including the baby, were among the refugees, he said.
