<HEAD>Ten Drug Traffickers Hanged in Public</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NICOSIA, Cyprus (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Iran hanged 10 convicted drug traffickers
Tuesday, Tehran radio reported.
   The 10 were convicted of smuggling into Iran 2,200 pounds of
opium and 12 ounces of heroin. Some also were found guilty of theft
and illegal possession of arms, according to the broadcast,
monitored in Nicosia.
   Tuesday's executions brought to 592 the number of alleged drug
traffickers executed since January, when a new law took effect that
mandates the death sentence for anyone caught in possession of even
small quantities of drugs.
   The anti-narcotics campaign came amid reports that 1 million
Iranians are believed involved in drug abuse nationwide.
