defendant who was paralyzed by gunfire on a Greenwich Village
street in February 1987.
   Alfano was one of 18 men convicted the following month of
participating in a Mafia-dominated, international drug trafficking
ring. The case was dubbed the ``pizza connection'' because the ring
allegedly used pizzerias as fronts for distributing an estimated
$1.6 billion in heroin over a decade.
   ``He (Spatola) admitted hiring the other participants'' in the
Alfano shooting, said Assistve unit. The Michigan
Democrat noted that former Defense Secretary Frank Carlucci had
announced withdrawal of the wing before NATO offered to help.
   Woodworth warned against that step, saying, ``We will harm
ourselves seriously with the allies.''
   Earlier, Robert Hale of the Congressional Budget Office told the
panels that the United States could save anywhere from $800 million
to $1.4 billion if it moves some of the active forces into
reserves. Hale said that would create be a ``modest'' reduction in
capability.
   The three panels considering the issue were the Senate Armed
Services subcommittees on manpower and personnel; readiness,
sustainability and support; and conventional forces and alliance
defense.
