<FILEID>AP-NR-05-16-89 1246EST</FILEID>
<FIRST>r f PM-Sears-Distribution     05-16 0185</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Sears-Distribution,0193</SECOND>
<HEAD>Giant Retailer's Merchandise Group to Spin Off Distribution Network</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CHICAGO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Sears, Roebuck and Co. has set up a separate
division for its warehousing and distribution operations, the
company announced.
   Michael Bozic, chairman of the Sears Merchandise Group, said
Monday that the group's distribution network has been will become a
wholly owned division of the Merchandise Group and will be called
Sears Logistics Services Inc.
   Bozic said the move is part of Sears' strategy to improve
efficiency and become more competitive. The company said it needs
better distribution to back up its new retail strategy based on
everyday low prices and more brand-name merchandise.
   Bozic said that at a later date the Terminal Freight Handling
Co., a transportation operation wholly owned by Sears, would be
merged with Sears Logistics Services to create a complete logistics
network under the aegis of the Merchandise Group.
   The latest distribution changes come two years after the
nation's largest retailer first began overhauling its warehousing
system.
   Since then, Sears has shut down five of its 12 major warehouses,
including an 82-year-old facility on Chicago's West Side.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
